çar","pron":"aw-sar'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to yoke or hitch; by analogy, to fasten in any sense, to join battle","kjv_def":"bind, fast, gird, harness, hold, keep, make ready, order, prepare, prison(-er), put in bonds, set in array, tie.","pos":"verb","usage":"bind(47x), prison(4x), tie(4x), prisoner(2x)"},"H632":{"id":"H632","lemma":"אֱסָר","translit":"ʼĕçâr","pron":"es-sawr'","derivation":"or אִסָּר; from H631 (אָסַר);","strongs_def":"an obligation or vow (of abstinence)","kjv_def":"binding, bond.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"bond(10x), binding(1x)"},"H633":{"id":"H633","lemma":"אֱסָר","translit":"ʼĕçâr","pron":"es-sawr'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H632 (אֱסָר) in a legal sense;","strongs_def":"an interdict","kjv_def":"decree.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"decree(7x)"},"H634":{"id":"H634","lemma":"אֵסַר־חַדּוֹן","translit":"ʼÊçar-Chaddôwn","pron":"ay-sar' Chad-dohn'","derivation":"of foreign derivation;","strongs_def":"Esar-chaddon, an Assyrian king","kjv_def":"Esar-haddon.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Esarhaddon(3x)"},"H635":{"id":"H635","lemma":"אֶסְתֵּר","translit":"ʼEçtêr","pron":"es-tare'","derivation":"of Persian derivation;","strongs_def":"Ester, the Jewish heroine","kjv_def":"Esther.","pos":"proper feminine noun","usage":"Esther(55x)"},"H636":{"id":"H636","lemma":"אָע","translit":"ʼâʻ","pron":"aw","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H6086 (עֵץ);","strongs_def":"a tree or wood","kjv_def":"timber, wood.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"timber(3x), wood(2x)"},"H637":{"id":"H637","lemma":"אַף","translit":"ʼaph","pron":"af","derivation":"a primitive particle;","strongs_def":"meaning accession (used as an adverb or conjunction); also or yea; adversatively though","kjv_def":"also, [phrase] although, and (furthermore, yet), but, even, [phrase] how much less (more, rather than), moreover, with, yea.","pos":"adverb, conjunction"},"H638":{"id":"H638","lemma":"אַף","translit":"ʼaph","pron":"af","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H637 (אַף)","strongs_def":"{meaning accession (used as an adverb or conjunction); also or yea; adversatively though}","kjv_def":"also.","pos":"conjunction","usage":"also(4x)"},"H639":{"id":"H639","lemma":"אַף","translit":"ʼaph","pron":"af","derivation":"from H599 (אָנַף);","strongs_def":"properly, the nose or nostril; hence, the face, and occasionally a person; also (from the rapid breathing in passion) ire","kjv_def":"anger(-gry), [phrase] before, countenance, face, [phrase] forebearing, forehead, [phrase] (long-) suffering, nose, nostril, snout, [idiom] worthy, wrath.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"anger(172x), wrath(42x), face(22x), nostrils(13x), nose(12x), angry(4x), before(2x), countenance(1x), forbearing(1x), forehead(1x), snout(1x), worthy(1x)"},"H640":{"id":"H640","lemma":"אָפַד","translit":"ʼâphad","pron":"aw-fad'","derivation":"a primitive root (rather a denominative from H646 (אֵפוֹד));","strongs_def":"to gird on (the ephod)","kjv_def":"bind, gird.","pos":"denominative verb","usage":"gird(1x), bound(1x)"},"H641":{"id":"H641","lemma":"אֵפֹד","translit":"ʼÊphôd","pron":"ay-fode'","derivation":"the same as H646 (אֵפוֹד) shortened;","strongs_def":"Ephod, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Ephod."},"H642":{"id":"H642","lemma":"אֵפֻדָּה","translit":"ʼêphuddâh","pron":"ay-food-daw'","derivation":"feminine of H646 (אֵפוֹד);","strongs_def":"a girding on (of the ephod); hence, generally, a plating (of metal)","kjv_def":"ephod, ornament.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"ephod(2x), ornament(1x)"},"H643":{"id":"H643","lemma":"אַפֶּדֶן","translit":"ʼappeden","pron":"ap-peh'-den","derivation":"apparently of foreign derivation;","strongs_def":"a pavilion or palace-tent","kjv_def":"palace.","pos":"masculine noun (of Persian origin)","usage":"palace(1x)"},"H644":{"id":"H644","lemma":"אָפָה","translit":"ʼâphâh","pron":"aw-faw'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to cook, especially to bake","kjv_def":"bake(-r, (-meats)).","pos":"verb","usa