":"an Ephrathite or an Ephraimite","kjv_def":"Ephraimite, Ephrathite.","pos":"proper adjective","usage":"Ephrathite(4x), Ephraimite(1x)"},"H674":{"id":"H674","lemma":"אַפְּתֹם","translit":"ʼappᵉthôm","pron":"ap-pe-thome'","derivation":"(Aramaic) of Persian origin;","strongs_def":"revenue; others at the last","kjv_def":"revenue.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"revenue(1x)"},"H675":{"id":"H675","lemma":"אֶצְבּוֹן","translit":"ʼEtsbôwn","pron":"ets-bone'","derivation":"or אֶצְבֹּן; of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Etsbon, the name of two Israelites","kjv_def":"Ezbon.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Ezbon(2x)"},"H676":{"id":"H676","lemma":"אֶצְבַּע","translit":"ʼetsbaʻ","pron":"ets-bah'","derivation":"from the same as H6648 (צֶבַע) (in the sense of grasping);","strongs_def":"something to sieze with, i.e. a finger; by analogy, a toe","kjv_def":"finger, toe.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"finger(32x)"},"H677":{"id":"H677","lemma":"אֶצְבַּע","translit":"ʼetsbaʻ","pron":"ets-bah'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H676 (אֶצְבַּע)","strongs_def":"{something to sieze with, i.e. a finger; by analogy, a toe}","kjv_def":"finger, toe.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"toe(2x), finger(1x)"},"H678":{"id":"H678","lemma":"אָצִיל","translit":"ʼâtsîyl","pron":"aw-tseel'","derivation":"from H680 (אָצַל) (in its secondary sense of separation);","strongs_def":"an extremity (Isaiah 41:9), also a noble","kjv_def":"chief man, noble.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"nobles(1x)"},"H679":{"id":"H679","lemma":"אַצִּיל","translit":"ʼatstsîyl","pron":"ats-tseel'","derivation":"from H680 (אָצַל) (in its primary sense of uniting);","strongs_def":"a joint of the hand (i.e. knuckle); also (according to some) a party-wall (Ezekiel 41:8)","kjv_def":"(arm) hole, great.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"great(1x)"},"H680":{"id":"H680","lemma":"אָצַל","translit":"ʼâtsal","pron":"aw-tsal'","derivation":"a primitive root; properly, to join; used only as a denominative from H681 (אֵצֶל);"